{{ "Completing blank links" | textToHeading('H2') }}

Two plugins ( `PageRstLinkerPlugin`_ and `PageHtmlLinkerPlugin`_ ) have been added to the basic configuration,
which process the text of the filled template before its result is written to a file, and fill in all empty links.

For example, an empty rst link of this format:

{{ '<pre>&lsquo;Existent page name&lsquo;_</pre>' | htmlToRst }}

will be replaced with this link:

{{ '<pre>&lsquo;Existent page name &#8249;/docs/some/page/targetPage.rst&#8250;&lsquo;_</pre>' | htmlToRst }}


And for HTML links like this:

{{ '<pre>&lt;a&gt;Existent page name&lt;/a&gt;</pre>' | htmlToRst }}

will be replaced with this link:

{{ '<pre>&lt;a href=&quot;/docs/some/page/targetPage.rst&quot;&gt;Existent page name&lt;/a&gt;</pre>' | htmlToRst }}


